radiographic_examinations.findings: A novel, heterozygous 3-kilobase deletion removing exons 7-9 of TP53 was detected in the patient's normal skin DNA, which was homozygous in the leukemia DNA due to uniparental disomy. A total of 28 validated somatic single-nucleotide variations or indels, 8 somatic structural variants, and 12 somatic copy number alterations were detected in the patient's leukemia genome.
Except for the deleted region (exons 7-9), TP53 mRNA expression was similar to or higher than that observed in AML without TP53 mutations.
Identified several complex chromosomal rearrangements in the leukemia genome.
